<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,352,2071]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,261,352,378]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
—The swamp habitat, silky fibrillose whitish pileus, clavate cheilo- and pleurocystidia, and basidiospores on average 6.6 × 4.8 µm, as well as exclusive the nrITS and nrLSU sequence data, are the key characters for separating 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kapitonov &amp; E. F. Malysheva" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,334,424,450]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="clavocystidiata">
<emphasis box="[136,334,424,450]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">V. clavocystidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
