<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,352,2071]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">
Two North American species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Murrill 1942: 145) Shaffer (1957: 568)" authorityName="Shaffer" authorityPageNumber="568" authorityYear="1957" baseAuthorityName="Murrill" baseAuthorityPageNumber="145" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[528,1126,1720,1747]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="alachuana">
<emphasis box="[528,673,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">V. alachuana</emphasis>
(Murrill 1942: 145) 
<bibRefCitation author="Shaffer, R. L." box="[906,1126,1720,1747]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" pagination="545 - 579" refId="ref5563" refString="Shaffer, R. L. (1957) Volvariella in North America. Mycologia 49 (4): 545 - 579." type="journal article" year="1957">Shaffer (1957: 568)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Shaffer 1957: 568)" baseAuthorityName="Shaffer" baseAuthorityPageNumber="568" baseAuthorityYear="1957" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="smithii">
<emphasis box="[1179,1283,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">V. smithii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shaffer, R. L." pageId="3" pageNumber="144" pagination="545 - 579" refId="ref5563" refString="Shaffer, R. L. (1957) Volvariella in North America. Mycologia 49 (4): 545 - 579." type="journal article" year="1957">Shaffer 1957: 568</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, are also characterized by silky fibrillose whitish pileus and white or pale-coloured volva. However, they differ in their ecological preferences (both occur in woods), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shaffer" authorityYear="1957" baseAuthorityName="Murrill" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[705,849,1792,1818]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="alachuana">
<emphasis box="[705,849,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">V. alachuana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has variable hymenial cystidia (lanceoloid, dumbbellshaped), and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Shaffer" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[286,390,1828,1854]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="smithii">
<emphasis box="[286,390,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">V. smithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has smaller spores (4.7–7.0 × 3.1–3.9 μm) and fusoid pleurocystidia with acute apex (
<bibRefCitation author="Shaffer, R. L." pageId="3" pageNumber="144" pagination="545 - 579" refId="ref5563" refString="Shaffer, R. L. (1957) Volvariella in North America. Mycologia 49 (4): 545 - 579." type="journal article" year="1957">Shaffer 1957</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,352,2071]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">
In the phylogenetic tree based on nrITS and nrLSU sequences (
<figureCitation box="[867,932,1900,1926]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1701,1723]" captionTargetBox="[152,1372,189,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[151,1436,175,1684]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2.—Best tree from the ML analysis of the nrITS-nrLSU data set for Volvariella with Cantharocybe gruberi as outgroup. Bootstrap support values and Posterior probability (BS/PP) are given above the branches.All tips are labelled with taxon name and accession numbers from GenBank or UNITE databases. For taxon in bold the sequences are generated in present study." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6333718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6333718/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Fig.2</figureCitation>
), the phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kapitonov &amp; E. F. Malysheva" authorityYear="2022" box="[1258,1452,1900,1926]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="clavocystidiata">
<emphasis box="[1258,1452,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">V.clavocystidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was clearly separated from other known species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spegazzini" authorityYear="1898" box="[747,870,1936,1962]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,870,1936,1962]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Volvariella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; it clustered with the sequence of 
<taxonomicName box="[1285,1451,1936,1963]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1285,1408,1936,1962]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Volvariella</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
<accessionNumber box="[136,259,1972,1998]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KR349630" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">KR349630</accessionNumber>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[334,392,1972,1998]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">India</collectingCountry>
but without any statistical support. In addition, the latter collection is likely to represent a different species due to large molecular differences between them (with percentage of genetic divergence in their nrITS sequences&gt;15 %).
</paragraph>
